1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
and it's been a number of weeks since we've had our last study

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:06,000
in the Wednesday night series, The Names of God.

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:10,000
And if you were keeping track of that particular series,

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:12,000
this would be lesson number 15

5
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:16,000
with regard to that series of The Names of God.

6
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,000
And as a reminder, we launched into this series

7
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:23,000
in order to develop a deeper understanding

8
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:25,000
of the nature and character of our God.

9
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:29,000
And I'm so thankful that God wants us to know Him.

10
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Isn't that wonderful?

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:34,000
And the reality is that we read of Moses and of Paul

12
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:37,000
making the statements that they wanted to know God

13
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,000
in a deeper, more intimate way.

14
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:42,000
And that ought to be the desire of every child of God,

15
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:47,000
that we desire to know Him in a deeper, more intimate way.

16
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,000
But if you think about it from the opposite perspective,

17
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:55,000
a great blessing is the fact that God wants us to know Him.

18
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:57,000
He has given to us a Bible.

19
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:01,000
He has given to us truth, and He's made it available to us.

20
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:04,000
And what we know to be true about God

21
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:08,000
is dependent upon our relationship with the Word of God.

22
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:10,000
And you know, there's a number of people

23
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,000
that don't know much about God.

24
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:13,000
They don't know who God is.

25
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,000
They have a wrong perspective of who God is

26
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,000
because they don't go to a Bible-preaching church.

27
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,000
They don't read a good Bible that reveals to them truth.

28
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:25,000
They're gathering their facts, their ideas

29
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:27,000
from other places, other sources.

30
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:29,000
And so we find that it's our desire

31
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:33,000
to have this deeper understanding of who our God is.

32
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:35,000
The psalmist declares, you remember this verse,

33
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,000
Psalm 9 and verse number 10?

34
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:39,000
And the psalmist says this,

35
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,000
And they that know thy name

36
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:46,000
will put their trust in thee.

37
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:49,000
And so you just pause and think about that for a moment.

38
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:52,000
They that know thy name

39
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:55,000
will put their trust in thee,

40
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:00,000
for thou, Lord, hast not forsaken them that seek thee.

41
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,000
And the reality is that as we know God

42
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:06,000
and we know Him in a deeper, more intimate way,

43
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:10,000
and we understand His character and His nature,

44
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:13,000
the more we will trust Him, the greater faith we will have.

45
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,000
Why?

46
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,000
Because we know the God of the impossible.

47
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:20,000
We know the God who can calm the storms.

48
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:23,000
We know the God who can move the mountains, amen?

49
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:27,000
And what a blessing to understand who He is.

50
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:30,000
This evening, our study will take us here

51
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:32,000
to Genesis chapter 16.

52
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:36,000
And we'll know a name that is actually representative here

53
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:39,000
of a interaction where the scriptures

54
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,000
are telling us about Hagar.

55
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,000
And Hagar uses this name,

56
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,000
and it's here in Genesis chapter 16.

57
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,000
And look in verse number 13,

58
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,000
and we'll catch the whole context here

59
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,000
in just a few moments.

60
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:51,000
But notice in verse 13, the Bible says,

61
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,000
and she, that's speaking of Hagar,

62
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,000
and she called the name of the Lord

63
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,000
that spake unto her,

64
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:02,000
thou, God, seest me.

65
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:06,000
For she said, have I also here looked after him

66
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:09,000
that seeth me?

67
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:13,000
El-Roy, that is the name that's here,

68
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,000
thou, God, seest me.

69
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:18,000
And so El-Roy, the God who sees me.

70
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:20,000
I want you to think about that just for a moment this evening

71
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,000
as we study through this passage

72
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:24,000
and look at a number of other portions of scripture.

73
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:26,000
And as we look here in Genesis chapter number 16,

74
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,000
if you're taking notes,

75
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:30,000
consider first of all what Hagar recognized.

76
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:33,000
In the midst of some very difficult circumstances,

77
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:36,000
the Lord appeared to her and spoke to her.

78
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:39,000
Begin reading with me in verse number one of this chapter.

79
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,000
Many of us are familiar with the passage.

80
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:44,000
The Bible says, now Sarai, Abram's wife,

81
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,000
bear him no children.

82
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,000
And she had a handmaid, an Egyptian,

83
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:50,000
whose name was Hagar.

84
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,000
We don't have time to develop all of this tonight,

85
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,000
but we understand that God had given a promise to Abraham

86
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:58,000
with regard to children,

87
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,000
with regard to a son, a child.

88
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:03,000
We understand also that when Abram

89
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,000
followed the leadership of God,

90
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,000
that he arrived in the land

91
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:09,000
and there was a time of famine

92
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,000
and he went to Egypt.

93
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:14,000
And no doubt in my mind,

94
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,000
as you study the scriptures,

95
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:17,000
where Hagar enters into the picture

96
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:19,000
is while they were down in Egypt

97
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,000
and they came out of Egypt

98
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,000
and Hagar is then with them.

99
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,000
Notice in verse two,

100
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,000
and Sarai said unto Abram,

101
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:31,000
behold now, the Lord hath restrained me from bearing.

102
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:35,000
I pray thee, go in unto my maid.

103
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:38,000
It may be that I may obtain children by her.

104
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:41,000
And Abram hearkened to the voice of Sarai.

105
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:44,000
And Sarai, Abram's wife, took Hagar,

106
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,000
her maid, the Egyptian,

107
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:49,000
after Abram had dwelt 10 years in the land of Canaan

108
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:54,000
and gave to her her husband Abram to be his wife.

109
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:57,000
And he went in unto Hagar and she conceived.

110
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:59,000
And when she saw that she had conceived,

111
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:02,000
her mistress was despised in her eyes.

112
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:05,000
In verse five, and Sarai said unto Abram,

113
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,000
my wrong be upon thee.

114
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:09,000
I have given my maid into thy bosom.

115
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:12,000
And when she saw that she had conceived,

116
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:14,000
I was despised in her eyes.

117
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:17,000
The Lord judged between me and thee.

118
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,000
But Abram said unto Sarai,

119
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,000
behold, thy maid is in thy hand.

120
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:23,000
Do to her as it pleaseth thee.

121
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:26,000
And when Sarai dealt hardly with her,

122
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:29,000
she fled from her face.

123
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,000
And I'm not, again, this evening,

124
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:33,000
I preached through Genesis 16 a while ago.

125
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:36,000
I'm not gonna deal with all of the contextual implications

126
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,000
of all that's going on,

127
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,000
but I want you to notice the difficult circumstances

128
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:42,000
in which Hagar finds herself.

129
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:45,000
And first of all, we understand that it was Sarai

130
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:48,000
that came up with the plan in verse number two.

131
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:52,000
It's not that Hagar was doing anything wicked or ungodly

132
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:55,000
and casting herself upon Abram.

133
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:58,000
We find, as we've read here in the context

134
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,000
with regard to what's happened,

135
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:02,000
we also acknowledge that Abram and Sarai

136
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:04,000
had been in the land for 10 years

137
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:06,000
and they'd had a promise from God

138
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:08,000
that had not yet been fulfilled.

139
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,000
And understand with me this evening

140
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:13,000
that God's timing is not always our timing

141
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:15,000
and we need to be careful not to get ahead of God

142
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:18,000
and not to depend on the flesh

143
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,000
and that's what's happened here.

144
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:24,000
And we find now that Sarai has this issue with Hagar

145
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:28,000
because she's now conceived and Sarai is barren.

146
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,000
And so we find in verse six at the end,

147
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,000
as I just read, that she, Sarai,

148
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:36,000
dealt hardly with her Hagar.

149
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,000
But notice verse seven.

150
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:42,000
The Bible says, and the angel of the Lord found her,

151
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:46,000
that's Hagar, by a fountain of water in the wilderness,

152
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:49,000
by the fountain in the way to Shur.

153
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:52,000
And he said, Hagar, Sarai's maid,

154
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:55,000
whence comest thou, camest thou, excuse me,

155
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:57,000
and whither wilt thou go?

156
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:00,000
And she said, I flee from the face of my mistress Sarai.

157
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:03,000
And the angel of the Lord said unto her,

158
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:07,000
return to thy mistress and submit thyself under her hands.

159
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,000
And the angel of the Lord said unto her,

160
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:13,000
I will multiply thy seed exceedingly,

161
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:16,000
but it shall not be numbered for multitude.

162
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,000
And the angel of the Lord said unto her,

163
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:20,000
behold, thou art with child,

164
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:24,000
and shalt bear a son, and shalt call his name Ishmael,

165
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:27,000
because the Lord hath heard thy affliction.

166
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,000
And he will be a wild man,

167
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:30,000
and will be against every man,

168
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:32,000
and every man's hand against him,

169
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:35,000
and he shall dwell in the presence of all his brethren.

170
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,000
And she, the verse that we read

171
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:39,000
by way of introduction this evening, verse 13,

172
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:42,000
and she called the name of the Lord,

173
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:46,000
that spake unto her, thou, God, seest me.

174
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:49,000
For she said, have I also here looked after him

175
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:51,000
that seeth me?

176
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:54,000
Wherefore, the well was called Beer-le-Hi-Roi.

177
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:57,000
Behold, it is between Kadesh and Bered.

178
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:59,000
And Hagar bare Abram a son,

179
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:01,000
and Abram called his son's name,

180
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:03,000
which Hagar bare Ishmael.

181
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,000
And Abram was fourscorn six years old

182
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:09,000
when Hagar bare Ishmael to Abram.

183
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,000
We consider what Hagar recognized

184
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:14,000
in the midst of these very difficult circumstances

185
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,000
that we've just read through the text of scripture,

186
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:20,000
that God appeared to her, and God spoke to her,

187
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,000
and she realized at that time,

188
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:24,000
as the Lord speaks to her,

189
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:27,000
she realized that though she felt helpless

190
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,000
and though she felt alone,

191
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:33,000
that God knew exactly where she was.

192
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,000
That not only did God know where she was,

193
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:37,000
but God knew what she was facing.

194
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,000
God knew her circumstances.

195
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:42,000
God knew all that had transpired.

196
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:45,000
God saw where she was.

197
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:48,000
And we begin to consider what she recognized

198
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,000
and how she responds in verse 13

199
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:53,000
by saying that she called the name of the Lord

200
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:56,000
that spake unto her, thou God, seest me.

201
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,000
And that's where we see the name tonight,

202
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:01,000
Elroi, the God who sees me.

203
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:04,000
You know, we look at the context here in Genesis 16

204
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,000
and the use of this name for God,

205
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:10,000
but I want you, as we consider what Hagar recognized

206
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:13,000
and seek to make some application in our own lives

207
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:16,000
with regard to the name of God, Elroi,

208
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:18,000
I want you to consider these truths

209
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:22,000
and rest in the God who sees you.

210
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,000
The God who sees you.

211
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,000
You ever heard somebody say,

212
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:27,000
no one knows, no one cares, no one sees,

213
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:29,000
no one understands?

214
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:32,000
And sometimes you hear people say those words.

215
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:36,000
Sometimes the circumstances of your life and my life

216
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:39,000
and the circumstances of those that we know,

217
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:40,000
sometimes that we're familiar with,

218
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:43,000
that we're maybe just simply acquainted with,

219
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:47,000
that they're dealing with some serious life circumstances.

220
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:50,000
And sometimes in the midst of those circumstances,

221
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:53,000
they can feel as if they're all alone.

222
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:58,000
They can feel as if no one understands, no one sees.

223
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,000
But I'm thankful this evening that.

224
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:05,519
though we can find ourselves in difficult times and difficult circumstances, that we

225
00:10:05,519 --> 00:10:12,159
can rest in the knowledge this evening that God gives us in his word that he is the God

226
00:10:12,159 --> 00:10:14,039
who sees.

227
00:10:14,039 --> 00:10:16,319
He's the God who sees.

228
00:10:16,319 --> 00:10:21,399
And that ought to bring for each of us this evening a measure of comfort that ought to

229
00:10:21,399 --> 00:10:29,559
cause us to rest in knowing that God sees, that God knows, that he's aware of.

230
00:10:29,559 --> 00:10:35,360
And to think about this truth this evening as we look at this name for God, and I understand

231
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:37,360
and we won't read any of the verses.

232
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:42,319
There's so many of them that we could turn to that it's hard to even just select a sampling

233
00:10:42,319 --> 00:10:43,319
of them.

234
00:10:43,319 --> 00:10:49,240
But throughout the era of Israel's history that we would refer to as the King era, in

235
00:10:49,240 --> 00:10:54,200
which you have all of the kings of Israel and Judah, and obviously you can study those

236
00:10:54,759 --> 00:11:01,240
through the book of 1 and 2 Samuel, 1 and 2 Kings, 1 and 2 Chronicles, and you can read

237
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:06,480
passage after passage of this era of Israel's history.

238
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:11,360
You'll note something that is repeated throughout those portions of scripture, and here's what's

239
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:15,480
repeated throughout there, and there are a number of references where the Bible speaks

240
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:24,120
of the king by name and says that their behavior, whether good or bad, in the eyes of the Lord.

241
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:25,760
In the eyes of the Lord.

242
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:32,519
And you'll see that oft repeated as it references the king and their behavior, and they did

243
00:11:32,519 --> 00:11:37,639
that which was right in the eyes of the Lord, in the sight of the Lord.

244
00:11:37,639 --> 00:11:41,519
They did that which was evil in the eyes of the Lord, in the sight of the Lord.

245
00:11:41,519 --> 00:11:46,160
And again, even as we would just reference so many of those portions of scripture this

246
00:11:46,160 --> 00:11:53,000
evening, and again not going to any of them in particular, but simply stating the fact

247
00:11:53,239 --> 00:11:58,080
that there are so many there that we could look to, the reality is that it makes us aware

248
00:11:58,080 --> 00:12:04,599
of the fact that God sees, that God knows, that He's aware.

249
00:12:04,599 --> 00:12:07,760
And you know, we live in a time in which it's kind of interesting.

250
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:10,160
I was thinking about this the last couple of days.

251
00:12:10,160 --> 00:12:14,919
There are times in which people will say something like I just said a moment ago, no one sees,

252
00:12:14,919 --> 00:12:19,039
no one understands, but then there are times that people do something and they say, I hope

253
00:12:19,039 --> 00:12:22,360
no one saw that.

254
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,360
You ever think about that?

