Delroy, the God who sees me, should be encouraged this evening that two sparrows are sold for

474
00:30:34,840 --> 00:30:41,600
a farthing, but not one of them is going to fall to the ground without our Father knowing.

475
00:30:41,600 --> 00:30:48,200
And he says, ye, ye are of more value than many sparrows. And you couple that truth with

476
00:30:48,200 --> 00:30:53,400
all of the verses that we looked at this evening, and you understand that God sees, He knows

477
00:30:53,400 --> 00:30:58,960
exactly where you are tonight. He knows what you're dealing with. He knows what no one

478
00:30:58,960 --> 00:31:08,319
else knows. He knows what you can't articulate. He knows. He sees. Hagar was in a very difficult

479
00:31:08,319 --> 00:31:16,720
situation. Many of those things that happened to her were not by her own choosing. But nonetheless,

480
00:31:16,720 --> 00:31:22,120
that's where she found herself. And tonight, there may be some things that you carry in

481
00:31:22,120 --> 00:31:27,520
your life, burdens that you have, that may not be directly because of sin in your life.

482
00:31:27,520 --> 00:31:32,000
It may not be because of something that you've done. Now, it could be that there's sin in

483
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:37,400
your life that's led to some hardship. But the reality this evening is that there are

484
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:42,040
times in which the circumstances around us are just outside of our control. They're not

485
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:46,959
outside of God's control. They're outside of our control. And if we're not careful,

486
00:31:46,959 --> 00:31:53,800
we can get discouraged and defeated. We can get that woe is me syndrome. Nobody sees.

487
00:31:53,800 --> 00:32:02,459
Nobody knows. Nobody understands. Nobody cares. But we must remember tonight that our God,

488
00:32:02,459 --> 00:32:11,119
one of the names, El Roy, He's the God who sees me. And tonight, rest in the truth that

489
00:32:11,119 --> 00:32:17,479
was recognized by Hagar. In the midst of those difficult circumstances, she recognized

490
00:32:17,479 --> 00:32:26,960
this beautiful truth and she called His name, El Roy. And this evening, be encouraged, rest

491
00:32:26,960 --> 00:32:32,760
in our God. Let's pray. Father, we love you. Thank you so much for loving us. Thank you

492
00:32:32,760 --> 00:32:41,559
for giving us a Bible. Thank you for allowing us to know you. God, I pray that you would

493
00:32:41,559 --> 00:32:51,160
help each of us this evening. Lord, I don't know all of the circumstances of all of the

494
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:57,839
people that are gathered here this evening, but I am thankful to know that you do. I'm

495
00:32:57,839 --> 00:33:05,880
thankful, God, that you see. And I hope, God, that we would rest and remember the words

496
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:12,839
of this song and any time that we hear it or sing it, that we'd remember that you are

497
00:33:12,839 --> 00:33:18,760
the God who sees me, El Roy. Bless our time of prayer. We thank you for the privilege.

498
00:33:18,760 --> 00:33:23,100
We thank you that you hear an answer, that you are able to do exceeding abundantly above

499
00:33:23,100 --> 00:33:27,860
all that we ask or think. And I pray that you would bless. We'll thank you for what

500
00:33:27,860 --> 00:33:34,139
you'll do. For it's in Christ's name we pray. Amen.

